grammar.treeinsertion.read

Class XMLHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
      • grammar.treeinsertion.read.XMLHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, org.xml.sax.DTDHandler, org.xml.sax.EntityResolver, org.xml.sax.ErrorHandler

    public class XMLHandler
extends org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
    Callback Handler for SAX-Parser. Parses from the XML-File a List of TIGRule for processing on later in the main parser.
    Author:
    Fabian Gallenkamp

      • startElement

        public void startElement(java.lang.String uri,
                java.lang.String localName,
                java.lang.String qName,
                org.xml.sax.Attributes attributes)
                  throws UnvalidXMLStructure
        Receive notification of the start/end of an element. Builds together with endElement(String, String, String) the tree for a grammar rule. Those tree rules are converted into TIGRule- Objects. Then they are added and stored in this object until the document is completely parsed.
        Specified by:
        startElement in interface org.xml.sax.ContentHandler
        Overrides:
